    "content": "nullManage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Manage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\n Salesforce Billing Patch Notes\n Salesforce Billing Installation\n Salesforce Billing Overview\n Preparing Your Salesforce Org for Billing\n Managing the Billing Order\n Usage Rating and Processing\n Invoice Generation\n Applying Taxes\n Payments and Credits\n Understanding the Revenue Recognition Process\n Closing and Reopening Finance Periods\n Reporting Essentials\n Finance Logging\n Salesforce Billing Tableau Dashboards\n Understand What Your Customers Have Bought by Using Customer Asset...\n View Changes to an Asset During Its Lifecycle\n How Lifecycle Management Works\n Invoicing Considerations When Using Customer Asset Lifecycle...\n Lifecycle Management Objects and Fields in Salesforce Billing\n Administer Customer Asset Lifecycle Management\n Printable Tip Sheets & User Guides — For Salesforce Billing\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALESFORCE BILLING\nUnderstand What Your Customers Have Bought by Using Customer Asset Lifecycle Management\n\nCustomer Asset Lifecycle Management gives you visibility into products your customers have bought, from initial sale through the end date of a subscription or service. As an account, sales, or service rep, you see an asset’s quantity, amount, and monthly recurring revenue at any point during an asset’s lifecycle. You can also see related invoice lines, the source of a change, and other information. Your business consolidates purchases and changes in one system, making subscriptions and other complex products easier to manage, and showing trends in a dashboard and reports. Developers or integrators automate creation of, changes to, and cancellation of lifecycle-managed assets using objects and fields that enhance the Asset object.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in Lightning Experience in Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with Salesforce CPQ Plus and Salesforce Billing\nView Changes to an Asset During Its Lifecycle\nView the current quantity, amount, and monthly recurring revenue (MRR) for an asset, and see trends throughout the asset’s lifecycle.\nHow Lifecycle Management Works\nAn asset without lifecycle management represents a product that a customer has bought, but the information stops at the time of sale. By contrast, a lifecycle-managed asset shows information about a product such as a subscription or a warranty after it’s sold. Customer Asset Lifecycle Management is driven by a custom automated process. For each lifecycle-managed asset, you see information in a dashboard and on related pages in Salesforce.\nInvoicing Considerations When Using Customer Asset Lifecycle Management\nThe Asset field is empty by default. When Salesforce Billing invoices an order through an invoice run or Bill Now, invoice lines inherit the value of the field. Review these considerations if you’re entering a value for the Asset field.\nLifecycle Management Objects and Fields in Salesforce Billing\nSome field values on asset lifecycle management objects are system populated, and some are API populated. You can’t customize asset lifecycle management fields or add custom fields to asset lifecycle management objects.\nAdminister Customer Asset Lifecycle Management\nYour developer or integrator uses the Connect REST API to automate creation of, changes to, and cancellation of lifecycle-managed assets. The system uses data from Salesforce or from third-party ecommerce, quoting, order management, and other applications. You grant permissions, set up page layouts, and customize the views of lifecycle-managed assets to support your business processes for account, sales, and service reps.\nSEE ALSO\nConnect REST API Developer Guide: Customer Asset Lifecycle Management\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
